Like a dream, psychosis opens up a flood of thoughts and fantasies that come from the deepest layers of consciousness.
The perception of reality in psychosis is focused on the subject, says Professor Thomas Fuchs, senior physician at the General Psychiatry Clinic of Heidelberg University Clinic.
Schizophrenics are at the center of events, everything has a meaning directed at them.
