Hallucinations belong to the typical accompanying phenomena of psychosis, but also to a surprising number of other diseases.
In addition to mental disorders such as borderline personality disorder or depression, diseases such as migraine, epilepsy, multiple sclerosis or Alzheimer’s or brain trauma are also common.
Surprisingly, under certain conditions, even the brain of a healthy person hallucinates.
