New tools for valuing cars
These days, storms and accidents are not only earned by car services.
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered an insurance event are pulled into service, where the expert must estimate the damage and repair costs.
No insurance event is the same and calculating the cost of parts and labor time can be a long and complicated job.
To calculate manually the repair costs from 20,000 to 30,000 euros including parts and labor can take two or three hours.
However, with the support of new computer tools, it would be a matter of minutes
Therefore, almost 100% of experts use this type of system.
Service providers and insurance event estimation and maintenance solutions are dedicated to collecting the information provided to them by manufacturers in order to then develop and offer their customers a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, of the American group Solera, is a leading company; 80% of the evaluations are carried out with its products.
Other companies that compete in the field of valuation and information preparation tools on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by the manufacturers is not easy at all.
According to Eduard Vel<0xC3><0xA1>zquez, Sales Director of Audatex, 63 manufacturers and importers work in Spain and each of them provides them with information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is still growing, as more versions, variants and engine solutions have been listed in the last five years than in the previous fifteen years.
As soon as a new vehicle enters the market, these companies will start working.
It is a very hot job, because it is necessary to catalog each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle and determine its price.
In addition, for each model, "intelligent" graphic processing is carried out, where it is possible to "push out" individual parts of tourist cars.
As for the model with massive sales, the work can be done in a week if the process is very fast.
As for the minority car, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models they have information about are Porsche, but not, for example, Ferrari or Lamborghini.
In terms of traffic fleets, they exceed 99%.
To carry out the work of documentation and database development, Audatex has eight centers distributed around the world (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in specific brands.
Its seat is in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (normally mechanical experts) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>90 million annually in the development of these databases.
Every month, 2.5 million data is entered and customers receive updates every two days.
The processing of this huge stream of information allows businesses to use and supply different products in different ways.
